The paper deals with the problem of multiple target tracking, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), and control systems (cs.SY). The approach proposed in the paper involves using Bayesian methods and density functions, which are also common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
